title: Waymo Expands Self-Driving Fleet with New US Manufacturing Facility

title: Waymo plans to double robotaxi production at Arizona plant by end of 2026
text: Waymo and the auto manufacturing giant Magna International plan to double robotaxi production at their new plant in Mesa, Arizona, by the end of 2026, the companies announced Monday. The "Waymo Driver Integration Plant," a 239,000 square foot facility outside of Phoenix, will assemble over 2,000 Jaguar I-PACE robotaxis by the end of 2026, the tech company said in a statement.

text: Alphabet's self-driving unit Waymo said on Monday that it plans to build Jaguar I-PACE and Zeekr vehicles with its autonomous technology at a new plant in Arizona as soon as this year, with Canadian auto parts supplier partner Magna International.

Despite market concerns, Alphabet's valuation is attractive, trading at a low PE multiple, with potential for multiple expansion and significant upside.

The deal, announced on Wednesday, marks the latest push by a major technology company to tap advanced nuclear power in support of artificial intelligence (AI) infrastructure, which is increasingly energy-intensive.
